The paper deals with the problem of designing covering codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of insertions and deletions as the metric for the covering codes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the analysis of lower and upper bounds, which is a common theme in coding theory (cs.CC) and discrete structures (cs.DS).
